---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Testing Methodology - AI Website Builders">

  <!-- BRUTALIST HERO - Coupon site style -->
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-[#FFF8F0]">
    <!-- Geometric accent -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[45%] h-full opacity-[0.04]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #F5521A 0px, #F5521A 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 w-32 h-32 bg-[#F5521A]/5 rounded-tr-[100px]"></div>

    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-7xl relative">
      <div class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-6">

          <!-- Brutalist badge -->
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(245,82,26,0.3)]">
            <div class="flex gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.15s"></span>
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-[#F5521A] rotate-45" style="animation-delay: 0.3s"></span>
            </div>
            <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-widest text-gray-800" style="font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;">
              4-STEP PROCESS • HANDS-ON TESTING
            </span>
          </div>

          <!-- MASSIVE headline -->
          <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl lg:text-7xl font-black leading-[0.9] tracking-tight text-gray-900">
            <span class="block">How I test</span>
            <span class="block text-[#F5521A] mt-2">AI website builders</span>
          </h1>

          <!-- Personal subheadline -->
          <div class="max-w-2xl">
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-gray-800/95 font-medium leading-relaxed">
              My testing process is designed to answer one question: <strong class="text-gray-900">What actually happens when you try to build a real website with this tool?</strong>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

	<!-- The Process - brutalist cards -->
	<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-white">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-12 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
        My testing process
      </h2>

			<div class="space-y-8">
				<div class="bg-white p-6 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]/20 relative overflow-hidden hover:border-[#F5521A]/50 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-[#F5521A] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-2xl">1</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Sign up and explore (1 hour)</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
                I create a real account, not a demo. I explore the interface, try the AI generation features,
                and note my first impressions. Is it intuitive? Confusing? Overwhelming?
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                <strong>I document:</strong> Sign-up process, onboarding flow, initial AI generation quality, UI clarity
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

				<div class="bg-white p-6 border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 hover:border-[#F5521A]/50 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-gray-900 text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-2xl">2</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-3">Build a real site (5-15 hours)</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
                This is the core of my testing. I don't just poke around—I build a complete, functional website.
                Portfolio, e-commerce, blog—whatever the tool is designed for.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                <strong>I document:</strong> AI generation quality, editing experience, template options, customization depth, every bug I hit
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

				<div class="bg-gray-900 p-6 border-[3px] border-transparent hover:border-[#F5521A]/30 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-[#F5521A] text-white flex items-center justify-center font-black text-2xl">3</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-3">Test the limits (2-4 hours)</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 mb-3">
                What happens when you push the tool? I add more pages, more content, more products.
                I try to export, test performance, check mobile responsiveness.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                <strong>I document:</strong> PageSpeed scores, export functionality, mobile experience, performance with 15+ pages, limits and paywalls
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

				<div class="bg-[#F5521A] p-6 border-[3px] border-[#D44A1A] shadow-[0_4px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.2)] hover:shadow-[0_6px_0_0_rgba(0,0,0,0.25)] hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all duration-300">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-6">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-16 h-16 bg-white text-[#F5521A] flex items-center justify-center font-black text-2xl">4</div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-white mb-3">Summarize findings (1 hour)</h3>
              <p class="text-white/80 mb-3">
                I compile everything into an honest review. What impressed me, what frustrated me,
                who this tool is actually for (not just "everyone!").
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-white/70">
                <strong>I document:</strong> Pros, cons, verdict, specific use cases, pricing breakdown, real examples from my testing
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- What we track - brutalist grid -->
	<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-gray-50">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
        What I track during testing
      </h2>
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
				<div class="bg-white p-5 border-[3px] border-gray-200">
					<h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 text-lg">Performance</h3>
					<ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
						<li>• PageSpeed Insights scores</li>
						<li>• Loading time with 5 pages</li>
						<li>• Loading time with 20 pages</li>
						<li>• Mobile performance</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-white p-5 border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300">
					<h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 text-lg">AI Quality</h3>
					<ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
						<li>• Content coherence (does it make sense?)</li>
						<li>• Design relevance</li>
						<li>• Hallucination rate (fake features)</li>
						<li>• Regeneration quality</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-gray-900 p-5 border-[3px] border-transparent">
					<h3 class="font-black text-white mb-4 text-lg">Usability</h3>
					<ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-400">
						<li>• Learning curve</li>
						<li>• Editor intuitiveness</li>
						<li>• Template variety</li>
						<li>• Customization depth</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-[#F5521A]/10 p-5 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]/20">
					<h3 class="font-black text-gray-900 mb-4 text-lg">Practical Concerns</h3>
					<ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
						<li>• Export functionality</li>
						<li>• Free plan limitations</li>
						<li>• Pricing transparency</li>
						<li>• Support quality</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Scoring - brutalist cards -->
	<section class="py-16 px-6 bg-white">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
			<h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-8 flex items-center gap-3">
        <div class="w-1 h-8 bg-[#F5521A]"></div>
        How I score
      </h2>
			<p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
				My scores out of 10 are based on weighted criteria that vary by tool type:
			</p>
			<div class="space-y-4">
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-5 bg-white border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]/20">
					<div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#F5521A] w-20">30%</div>
					<div class="flex-1">
						<div class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Ease of use</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Learning curve, editor quality, intuitiveness</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-5 bg-white border-[3px] border-gray-200">
					<div class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 w-20">25%</div>
					<div class="flex-1">
						<div class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Design quality</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-gray-600">AI generation aesthetics, template variety</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-5 bg-white border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300">
					<div class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 w-20">20%</div>
					<div class="flex-1">
						<div class="font-black text-gray-900 text-lg">Features</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-gray-600">E-commerce, blogging, SEO, analytics</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-5 bg-gray-900">
					<div class="text-3xl font-black text-[#F5521A] w-20">15%</div>
					<div class="flex-1">
						<div class="font-black text-white text-lg">Performance</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-gray-400">PageSpeed, loading times, mobile scores</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-4 p-5 bg-[#F5521A]">
					<div class="text-3xl font-black text-white w-20">10%</div>
					<div class="flex-1">
						<div class="font-black text-white text-lg">Value</div>
						<div class="text-sm text-white/80">Pricing relative to features, free plan quality</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- Brutalist CTA -->
	<section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gray-900 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03]" style="background-image: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #fff 0px, #fff 1px, transparent 1px, transparent 12px);"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-3xl relative">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-white leading-tight mb-6">
          Full transparency
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-400 mb-8">
          I document everything. Screenshot every bug. Track every loading time.
          If a tool pays me for a placement (none do currently), I'll clearly label it as "Sponsored."
        </p>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 border-[3px] border-[#F5521A]/20">
          <p class="text-gray-900 font-black mb-2">My promise:</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
            I will never accept payment for positive reviews. I will never let affiliate relationships influence my scores.
            If I have an affiliate link, I'll clearly mark it.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>